<TITLE> 'Manzur to purge CCC of corruption' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 7(bdnews24.com)  The Chittagong City Corporation would be purged of corruption, nepotism and partisanship if the BNP-backed mayoral candidate wins. BNP vice chairman Abdullah Al Noman made the statements when he was campaigning Manzur Alam in different parts of the port city on Monday. Noman said, "Those who were in power misused it. So the culture of corruption will have to be uprooted through change." Noman campaigned at Halishahar, Badamtali, Abdul para, South Kattli, Failla Bazar, Pranharidas Road, Saraipara, Pahartali, Kazi Dhigirpar, Sagorika Road. During the campaign seeking votes for his symbol, pineapple, Manzur said, "I seek vote from you for the development of Chittagong." He said, "You, the people will remain alert on election day to prevent any attempt of vote rigging." "I want to relieve the city corporation of problems which have accumulated over the last 17 years," he said. Jamaat-e-Islami leader Shahjahan Chowdhury, Afsar Uddin and BJP leader Jahangir Alam were among others present during the campaign. b
